core.conflict

Interface IConflictScope<T,E>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of entities that define this conflict scope.
    E - The type of entities that underly the conflict incurred by the conflict source entity of this conflict scope.
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractConflictScope, GeneralizationAdaptationClassAssociationConflictScope, GeneralizationAdaptationClassAttributeConflictScope, GeneralizationAdaptationClassDependencyConflictScope

    public interface IConflictScope<T,E>
    an IConflictScope generic interface that defines a conflict scope entity.

    For a given conflict domain, if a conflict arises, then it must occur in a conflict scope within the conflict domain in hand. A conflict scope, for example, can designate a set of a classes within a generalization hierarchy.

    If a conflict arises, then it is caused by a conflict source entity, having the same type as the entities defining a conflict scope for a conflict domain.

    It must be implemented by any concrete class designating a conflict scope.
    Author:
    Bachar Rima
    See Also:
    IConflictDomain, AbstractConflictSource, AbstractConflictScope
